EoN Resorts Group is a world class luxury resort owner and developer based in Maldives and over the past 10 years, the company has developed some of the world's most prestigious hotels in Maldives.  The proposed investment in Colombo includes mainly the following:

 45 storyed luxury hotel catering to both leisure and business tourists;


300 luxury hotel rooms ;


100 luxury residencies ;


Convention Centre capable of hosting 2000 guests ;

The above Joint proposal made by Hon. Rajitha Senaratne, Minister of Fisheries and Aquatic Resources Development; and Hon. Lakshman Yapa Abeywardana, Minister of Investment Promotion to proceed with the project, was approved by the Cabinet.

Cabinet of Ministers noted the information on achievement at National, Provincial, District and Zonal levels, based on the results of the G.C.E. (O/L) Examination - 2012, submitted by Hon. Bandula Gunawardena, Minister of Education.   According to the analysis - 

64.74% of the students who sat for the G.C.E. (O/L) Examination, 2012 have qualified to study for the G.C.E. (A/L). This is an increase of 15.04% from 2005 - 2012 ;


the percentage of students who have failed in all the subjects which was 8.02% in 2005 has decreased to 4.13% in 2012 ;


the percentage of students qualified in 2012 to follow A/L classes in the Eastern, Northern and Uva Provinces has increased by 5.8%, 5.73% and 5.81% respectively, when compared with that of 2011;

the two proposals made by H.E. the President, in his capacity as the Minister of Ports and Highways, to proceed with the activities relating to the rehabilitation and improvements of the following road sections, were approved by the Cabinet.


from Peliyagoda to Mahabage (from 0.6 km to 9.0 km) and


