- the above Annual Report submitted by H.E. the President, in his capacity as the Minister of Finance and Planning, was approved by the Cabinet for presentation in Parliament.  Some of its salient features are as follows:

*  	the Sri Lankan economy grew at a healthy rate of 6.4% in 2012;

*  	inflation was contained at a single digit level at 7.6%;

*  	investment as a percentage of GDP was 30.6%;

*  	the external sector strengthened during the year benefiting from the policy measures that were adopted in early 2012 to improve macroeconomic stability;

*  	the agriculture sector grew by 5.8% in 2012;  

*  	the industry sector grew by 10.3% during the year, contributing substantially to the expansion of the economy in 2012; and 

*  	remittances by migrant workers increased by 16.3% to US $6 billion during the year, continuing to be the largest single source of foreign exchange inflow to Sri Lanka.

the proposal made by Hon. Wimal Weerawansa, Minister of Construction, Engineering Services, Housing and Common Amenities, to expend a sum of Rs.15.6 million for the renovation of housing units under the National Housing Development Authority and to meet the  housing needs of the low income community in the city of Colombo and for the implementation of  the undermentioned projects aimed at offering a better living standard to the people living in the relevant areas, was approved by the Cabinet:

*	renovation of housing units under the National Housing Development Authority at a cost of Rs.5.6 million; and;

*	development of infrastructure facilities of the under-served settlements in the city of Colombo at a cost of Rs.10 million.

- the proposal made by Hon. (Dr.) Jagath Balasuriya, Minister of National Heritage, to establish the above fund, utilizing Rs.100 million approved in the Budget Proposals for 2012 as an initial capital of the fund, was approved by the Cabinet. The main objectives of establishing the above fund are as follows:

*	preservation of  archeological sites etc. of historical value;

* 	exploration and excavation of archeological sites and conservation of old paintings;

*	promotion of our heritage and provision of related information for foreign as well as local tourists; and

*	organization of exhibitions, printing of publications, production of audio-visual documentaries, conducting of workshops etc. to enhance the knowledge of the people regarding the preservation of archeological heritage for the future generation.

- the proposal made by H.E. the President, in his capacity as the Minister of Finance and Planning, to hold a Tax Week annually in order to create awareness among the public in respect of the Government Tax System and to declare the Tax Week from 01st to 08th November 2012, was approved by the Cabinet.  Its main objectives are as follows:

*	increase the awareness of the tax system among the public;

*	building public confidence in tax administration and related activities of the Departments of Inland Revenue and Sri Lanka Customs, whereby voluntary compliance with the taxes by the public could be encouraged;

*	enlighten the public of the contribution they could render towards future prosperity of the country through timely payment of taxes;

*	make the public aware of the tax reliefs and tax holidays granted by the new tax system which is being implemented since 2011;

- Cabinet considered  the recommendations of the Officials' Committee appointed for the purpose and approval was granted to implement the following recommendations of the Committee:

*	identification and mapping of fire prone areas in each District and preparation of Fire Management Plans for such areas;

*	supply of required resources, through the respective District Secretaries, to the Forest Department and the Department of Wildlife Conservation to ensure effective fire control programmes;

*	to advise the law enforcement authorities (Police and Armed Forces) to be vigilant, specially during the dry season, in order  to apprehend those responsible for initiating forest fires; and

*	conduct training and awareness programmes on fire management for communities and relevant stakeholders in the areas,

- theproposal made by  H.E. the President, in his capacity as the Minister of Defence and Urban Development,  to implement the following projects in stages, was approved by the Cabinet: 

*	refurbishment of Old Dutch Hospital building at Colombo Fort;
*	renovation work of Old Marketing Department Building at Colombo Fort; 
*	development of Race Course Grounds and Bloomfield Grounds;
*	refurbishment of Central Super Market, Pettah (former fish market);
*	development of Independence Square;
*	re-location of Manning Market to Peliyagoda; 
*	re-development of existing Manning Market premises for the expansion of bus stand and to accommodate informal sector within a Commercial Complex area.   
	The construction work of these projects will be entrusted to the Engineering 	Services Divisions of the Sri Lanka Army, Navy and Air Force so that the cost of 	construction could be kept to a minimum.

